bilingual.source: His face is full of dirt spots.
bilingual.target: 他的脸上有斑斑的泥土。

bilingual.source: There is some dirt on the child's face.
bilingual.target: 孩子的脸皮上有些泥土。

bilingual.source: The child's feet are playing in the dirt.
bilingual.target: 孩子的脚丫在泥土里玩耍。

bilingual.source: The nozzle of the hose was clogged with dirt.
bilingual.target: 水管的喷嘴被泥土堵住了。

bilingual.source: The nozzel of the hose was clogged with dirt.
bilingual.target: 水管的喷嘴被泥土堵住了。

bilingual.source: He is cleaning the dirt from the wheel housing.
bilingual.target: 他正在清洗轮罩里的泥土。

bilingual.source: They found a trace of dirt on the floor.
bilingual.target: 他们在地板上发现了泥土的印记。

bilingual.source: The unwashed car was covered in dirt and grime.
bilingual.target: 这辆未洗的车上满是泥土和污垢。

bilingual.source: The dirt caked on the car after the off-road trip.
bilingual.target: 越野旅行后泥土覆盖着一层硬壳在车上。

list.abstract: Dirt是马修-卡纳罕(Matthew Carnahan)导演的一部影片，主演是柯特妮-考克斯，伊恩-哈特，乔什-斯图沃特，第莫希-包特姆斯，安柯-巴特，埃里克-瑞霍特。2007年01月02日首映。
《Dirt》是Florida Georgia Line于2014年7月8日发行的单曲，作为其2014年录音室专辑《Anything Goes》的首支主打单曲。

yingyinNormal.en: I like dirt and rocks and facts. No argument here.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我更喜欢脚踏实地货真价实。这我也同意。

yingyinNormal.en: Heck, give me a peck of dirt any day of the week.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那随时给我盖一把黄土吧。

yingyinNormal.en: You've got dirt on your nose by the way. Did you know?
yingyinNormal.zh: 对了，你鼻子有块脏东西，你知道吗？

yingyinNormal.en: That thing's made of dirt. Are we sure it didn't just rain?
yingyinNormal.zh: 那里都是用土建起来的。你确定不是只是下雨而已吗？

yingyinNormal.en: Give it too much, you'll be outta the dirt and into the tulips.
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果你开太快的话就会滑出去

yingyinNormal.en: What 12-year-old boy wants a motorized dirt bike? All of them? Really? Yeah.
yingyinNormal.zh: 一个怎么样的12岁男孩会要辆摩托车？所有的。真的？是的。

yingyinNormal.en: A radioactive buried under dirt as if it had never existed like District 13.
yingyinNormal.zh: 放射性物质弥漫全城，只剩下死亡，如同消失的13区。

yingyinNormal.en: One day, you will perish. You will lie with the rest of your kind in the dirt.
yingyinNormal.zh: 终有一天你将消亡，你将和自己的同类一起葬于黄土之下。

yingyinNormal.en: Hi. I'm gal pal Rachel Green, and if you want the dirt, I'm the one you come too.
yingyinNormal.zh: 嗨，我是女性朋友瑞秋格林，你想知道八卦消息就来找我，这可能是乔伊的孩子，谁知道呢？

yingyinNormal.en: How a boy grew up in a dirt-poor shithole and climbed his way out through hard work.
yingyinNormal.zh: 一位出身贫寒的少年是如何努力工作攀上人生巅峰。

yingyinNormal.en: This ain't asphalt, son. This is dirt. Oh, great. What do you want? You here to gloat?
yingyinNormal.zh: 这不是柏油路，这是泥路。唉，你又想要干嘛？你是来炫耀的吗？

yingyinNormal.en: He'd been left with the ability to play the gentleman, but he was once again dirt-poor.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他表面上还能继续扮绅士，但实际上，他又一次身无分文了。

yingyinNormal.en: Did you even hear the dirt that happened over break? Who would I have heard it from? Dorota?
yingyinNormal.zh: 假期里你有没听说到一些八卦新闻？你说我可以从谁那里打听？朵箩塔吗？

yingyinNormal.en: His parents were dirt-poor farmers from North Dakota. But he never accepted them as his parents at all.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他的父母是北达科他州身无分文的农民，但他从不认他们为自己的父母。

yingyinNormal.en: Come on, you guys. Tell me all the dirt. Well, the biggest news is still you dumping Barry at the altar.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好了，你们快点跟我讲八卦。最大的八卦，还是你在圣坛前抛下贝瑞。

yingyinNormal.en: Anything you can find, dirt or past arrests. Maybe he has a drinking problem. I am not a dirty stinking Jew!
yingyinNormal.zh: 丑事，被捕记录，什么都要，或许他还酗酒，我才不是肮脏恶心的犹太人。

yingyinNormal.en: Really bad bumpy dirt road, Riley, with no lights and a cliff, and some sort of weird hitchhiker with a banjo!
yingyinNormal.zh: 你干嘛非得选这条路走啊，又脏又崎岖，在悬崖边，没有灯，路边还有拿着班卓琴想搭便车的怪人！

yingyinNormal.en: Then my friends are there. Covered in dirt and grass eaten by worms. I don't want to have to visit my sons here.
yingyinNormal.zh: 然后吾友们长眠于此，泥草覆身，虫蛆啃噬。我不想探望我崽于此。

yingyinNormal.en: Instead of a titanium centrifuge, my parents bought me, wow, this is hard. They got me a motorized dirt bike. No!
yingyinNormal.zh: 然而我父母却给我买了一个...真是难以启齿，他们给我买了一辆摩托车。不会吧。

yingyinNormal.en: Hear. To a peck of dirt. Hear. I will drink to that, but I will also drink to the general, a good servant. To the general.
yingyinNormal.zh: 说得好。敬黄土。说得好。我要敬这一杯，也要敬将军一杯他是位优秀的公仆。敬将军。

examination_example.sentence: That's about as effective as brushing <highlight>dirt</highlight> under a carpet and can even make us ill.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这就像在地毯下刷灰尘一样有效，甚至会让我们生病。

examination_example.sentence: Pyle was famous for covering the human side of the war, writing about the <highlight>dirt</highlight>-snow-and-mud soldiers, not how many miles were gained.
examination_example.sentence_trans: Pyle以报道战争的人性方面而闻名，他写的是在肮脏的雪和泥中作战的士兵，而不是行军了多少英里。

examination_example.sentence: Both men emphasized the <highlight>dirt</highlight> and exhaustion of war, the fragments of civilization that the soldiers shared with each other and the civilians.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 两人都强调战争的硝烟和耗损，以及士兵们和民众共享的文明片段。

examination_example.sentence: The more <highlight>dirt</highlight> you track in, the more it scratches and the more often you'd have to clean.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你踩进去的脏东西越多，刮伤的地方就越多，你需要清理的次数也就越多。

examination_example.sentence: "We are treating the <highlight>dirt</highlight> as an art piece," says Rong Bo, the museum's leading archeologist.

examination_example.sentence: Archeologists are also finding colors in the <highlight>dirt</highlight> around the soldiers.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 考古学家还在士兵周围的泥土中发现了颜色。

examination_example.sentence: It's important not to do anything with the <highlight>dirt</highlight>, so the colors won't be lost.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 重要的是不要处理这些污垢，这样颜色就不会丢失。
